<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued April 29 at 6:30PM CDT until April 29 at 7:00PM CDT by NWS Saint Louis</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 700 PM CDT
FOR SOUTHEASTERN PIKE COUNTY IN WEST CENTRAL ILLINOIS...
At 630 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 11 miles northeast
of Belleview, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.
Locations impacted include...
Bedford, Montezuma and Nebo.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;50 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
